        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Hi friends \xf0\x9f\x91\x8b,
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Happy Thursday! Hope you had a great long weekend and that your summer is off to an excellent start.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         <span>
          Not Boring\xe2\x80\x99s mission is to make the world more optimistic. On that quest, we\xe2\x80\x99ve written about everything from
         </span>
         <a href="https://substack.com/redirect/9665f377-1ada-4280-abe4-79bd898af0b5?j=eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel="" style="color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">
          fusion
         </a>
         <span>
          to
         </span>
         <a href="https://substack.com/redirect/db8e2e1e-6c5b-4593-a23b-883275ce6951?j=eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel="" style="color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">
          AI-driven drug discovery
         </a>
         <span>
          . These are big, bold, sexy bets that, if successful, will make the world a fundamentally better place.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         <span>
          But sometimes, the solutions are simpler. Ezra, the subject of today\xe2\x80\x99s piece, believes that
         </span>
         <strong>
          early detection is the cure for cancer
         </strong>
         <span>
          . It\xe2\x80\x99s on its own mission to decrease the cost and increase the accessibility of cancer screening in order to catch cancer early, when it\xe2\x80\x99s easier to treat. A world in which cancer no longer claims millions of lives annually would be a fundamentally better place.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         <span>
          Today\xe2\x80\x99s essay is a Sponsored Deep Dive, and one of the ones I\xe2\x80\x99m proudest to bring you in Not Boring\xe2\x80\x99s history. In the spirit of not writing about anything I wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t do myself, I got screened a few weeks ago, and I\xe2\x80\x99m glad I did. You can read more about how I choose which companies to do deep dives on, and how I write them
         </span>
         <a href="https://substack.com/redirect/d340ede2-6e98-4646-9472-64515274b89a?j=eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel="" style="color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">
          here
         </a>
         <span>
          .
         </span>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Let\xe2\x80\x99s get to it.
        </p>
        <div style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;">
         <hr style="background: #e0e0e0; border: none; height: 1px; margin: 32px 0; padding: 0;"/>
        </div>
        <h1 class="header-with-anchor-widget" style="-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility; -moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; appearance: optimizelegibility; color: #404040; font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 2em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position: relative;">
         <strong>
          Ezra: The Quest to Kill Cancer
         </strong>
        </h1>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 32px auto;">
         <figure style="margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" data-component-name="Image2ToDOMStatic" style="mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
           <tbody>
            <tr>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
             <td align="left" class="content" style="text-align: center;" width="1200">
              <a class="image-link" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F29362d05-4e50-4150-9f17-cf572085e37c_1200x600.png" rel="" style="align-items: center; border: none; display: block; flex-direction: column; height: auto; margin: 0; padding: 0; position: relative; text-decoration: none; width: auto;" target="_blank">
               <img alt="" class="wide-image" data-attrs='{"src":"https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/29362d05-4e50-4150-9f17-cf572085e37c_1200x600.png","fullscreen":null,"imageSize":null,"height":600,"width":1200,"resizeWidth":null,"bytes":342827,"alt":null,"title":null,"type":"image/png","href":null,"belowTheFold":true,"topImage":false,"internalRedirect":null}' height="275" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_2400,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F29362d05-4e50-4150-9f17-cf572085e37c_1200x600.png" style="-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none !important; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0 auto; margin-bottom: 0; max-width: 100% !important; vertical-align: middle; width: auto !important;" width="550"/>
              </a>
             </td>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
            </tr>
           </tbody>
          </table>
         </figure>
        </div>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Let\xe2\x80\x99s start in the future. Pick a year, say 2050.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         In the year 2050, each time you step in front of the mirror in your bedroom, it runs a quick and dirty MRI on you. The MRI won\xe2\x80\x99t be as high-resolution as something you would have gotten in a tube in 2023, but it doesn\xe2\x80\x99t need to be. AI fills in the gaps and pulls signal from noise.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 32px auto;">
         <figure style="margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" data-component-name="Image2ToDOMStatic" style="mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
           <tbody>
            <tr>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
             <td align="left" class="content" style="text-align: center;" width="908">
              <a class="image-link" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F23fca300-5dea-498b-af62-9b26f1206b74_908x458.png" rel="" style="align-items: center; border: none; display: block; flex-direction: column; height: auto; margin: 0; padding: 0; position: relative; text-decoration: none; width: auto;" target="_blank">
               <img alt="" class="wide-image" data-attrs='{"src":"https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/23fca300-5dea-498b-af62-9b26f1206b74_908x458.png","fullscreen":null,"imageSize":null,"height":458,"width":908,"resizeWidth":null,"bytes":null,"alt":null,"title":null,"type":null,"href":null,"belowTheFold":true,"topImage":false,"internalRedirect":null}' height="277.42290748898677" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1816,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F23fca300-5dea-498b-af62-9b26f1206b74_908x458.png" style="-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none !important; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0 auto; margin-bottom: 0; max-width: 100% !important; vertical-align: middle; width: auto !important;" width="550"/>
              </a>
             </td>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
            </tr>
           </tbody>
          </table>
         </figure>
        </div>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Most days \xe2\x80\x93 99.9% of days \xe2\x80\x93 you don\xe2\x80\x99t even remember you\xe2\x80\x99re being scanned. There\xe2\x80\x99s nothing to report, so your mirror reports nothing.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Very occasionally, though, it might notice enough of a change in your cells that it recommends a higher-resolution, localized scan on, say, your prostate, moves some things around on your calendar, books you an appointment, and summons your car to whisk you away to an imaging facility for a closer look.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         The facility runs a prostate scan, AI flags the relevant parts, a radiologist reads them, and a doctor tells you the three words that used to be among the most devastating in any language: \xe2\x80\x9cYou have cancer.\xe2\x80\x9d
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         They follow up, however, with words that have become commonplace: \xe2\x80\x9cIt\xe2\x80\x99s very early, the earliest stages of Stage 1, and we can cut it out.\xe2\x80\x9d Your car whisks you to a nearby facility where surgeons, armed with a precise, 3D map of your tumor\xe2\x80\x99s location in the prostate, snip it out before it has the chance to spread. Minutes later, a doctor delivers the good news: \xe2\x80\x9cYou are cancer-free.\xe2\x80\x9d The doctor prescribes a personalized immunotherapy to head-off the chance of remission. You go on living your life.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Unfortunately, this is not the world we live in today.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         As it stands, cancer is the second-leading cause of death in the United States, behind heart disease, and the number of cancer deaths continues to grow annually.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 32px auto;">
         <figure style="margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
