        </div>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         I\xe2\x80\x99d steeled myself against the idea that it would find something, and that because I was asymptomatic, it would probably be early and local, and so we would just cut it out and move on. Reading \xe2\x80\x9cno evidence of cancer\xe2\x80\x9d felt inaccurate for a minute. I clicked around to confirm that I wasn\xe2\x80\x99t missing something. When it sank in, it was just a huge relief.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         <span>
          The scan uncovered a couple of things \xe2\x80\x93 \xe2\x80\x9cLow-lying cerebellar tonsils without pegging\xe2\x80\x9d and \xe2\x80\x9cFrontal sinus and bilateral ethmoid sinus mucosal thickening\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x93 but the
         </span>
         <strong>
          AI-generated report
         </strong>
         <span>
          explained each in plain English:
         </span>
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 32px auto;">
         <figure style="margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" data-component-name="Image2ToDOMStatic" style="mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
           <tbody>
            <tr>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
             <td align="left" class="content" style="text-align: center;" width="912">
              <a class="image-link" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F43794187-cc10-437b-af2d-ee838b5d79ba_912x572.png" rel="" style="align-items: center; border: none; display: block; flex-direction: column; height: auto; margin: 0; padding: 0; position: relative; text-decoration: none; width: auto;" target="_blank">
